<TITLE> 'Few' new BNP leaders gather at Zia's grave </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 9 (bdnews24.com)  The newly elected BNP national executive committee, led by the party's secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain, on Saturday placed wreaths and offered prayers at Ziaur Rahman's grave. Though it was meant to be attended by all 386 executive members, the new BNP leaders were largely absent at the programme. Only 10 among the 32 members of the advisory council and just four among the 15 vice-presidents of the national executive committee were present at Zia's graveside. Excepting Fakhrul Islam, no other joint secretary general of the total seven attended the occasion. bd
